Defendant Nicholas J Janecek in court with Attorney Patricia M. Padurean.  Kristi J Gordon appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count #1.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #1. State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Padurean makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:  IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

12 MONTHS JAIL - 1st 90 Days Straight Time - remainder with Huber

TERM OF PROBATION:  18 MONTHS   -  Transfer allowed to Milwaukee County 

CONDITIONS OF PROBATON:  
____AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
____Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
____No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs 
____No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
____Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are 
prescribed/sign releases
____Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
____Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
____DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done 

COSTS:  $268.00 & $250.00 DNA surcharge  (to be paid as a condition of probation)

** Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department**

CONDITION TIME:   30 Days, Non-working hours with standard release conditions - STAYED - to be used at agent's discretion

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
